20/12/2004
TETOVO, Macedonia -- Abduladi Vejseli was elected the new leader of the opposition Party for Democratic Prosperity during the party congress in Tetovo on Saturday (18 December).
Vejseli was the sole candidate for the post, after Abdulmenaf Bexheti decided to withdraw from the chairmanship for personal reasons.
In other news, Macedonia's border police were expected to complete the process of taking over control over the eastern border with Bulgaria on Monday, and to start assuming control over the northern border with Serbia.
The entire process of transferring border management responsibilities from the army to the police is set to finish by 2006.
(Utrinski Vesnik, Makfax - 20/12/04;
Dnevnik, Makfax, A1 TV - 18/12/04)
